; IONA'S `@` SETS THE RESULT BUT DOES NOT EXIT THE FUNCTION. EXECUTION
; CONTINUES TO THE END, SO RESOURCE-CLEANUP STATEMENTS PLACED AFTER A `@`
; ALWAYS GET A CHANCE TO RUN -- THE LANGUAGE HAS NO DESTRUCTORS.

!READSQUARED W, X W
    "OPEN FILE" PRINT
    X X * @               ; SET THE RESULT WE WANT TO HAND BACK
    "CLOSE FILE" PRINT    ; STILL RUNS, EVEN THOUGH WE ALREADY "RETURNED"

!MAIN W
    5 READSQUARED PRINT
